  <title>Responsive Layout with Grid and Flexbox</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header class="header">
      <h1>My Responsive Website</h1>
    </header>

    <nav class="nav">
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Services</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Portfolio</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <main class="main-content">
      <section class="intro">
        <h2>Welcome to our website</h2>
        <p>
          This is an example of a responsive layout using CSS Grid for the base structure and Flexbox for navigation and cards alignment.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="cards">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Card #1</h3>
          <p>This is a card using Flexbox layout inside the main content.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Card #2</h3>
          <p>This card adjusts its size and alignment with Flexbox.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Card #3</h3>
          <p>Cards stack or wrap as screen size changes.</p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>

    <aside class="sidebar">
      <h3>Sidebar</h3>
      <p>Additional links, info, or advertisements can go here.</p>
      <ul>
